#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:4319
msgid "Command alias"
msgstr "Alias de commande"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:4320
msgid "You can set an alias for the frequently used command."
msgstr "Vous pouvez définir des alias pour les commandes fréquemment utilisées."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:4322
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ alias la='ls -la'"
msgstr "$ alias la='ls -la'"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:4323
msgid "Now, \"<literal>la</literal>\" works as a short hand for \"<literal>ls -la</literal>\" which lists all files in the long listing format."
msgstr "Maintenant, «&nbsp;<literal>la</literal>&nbsp;» fonctionnera comme un raccourci pour «&nbsp;<literal>ls -la</literal>&nbsp;» qui donne la liste de tous les fichier dans le format de liste long."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:4324
msgid "You can list any existing aliases by <literal>alias</literal> (see <literal>bash</literal>(1) under \"SHELL BUILTIN COMMANDS\")."
msgstr "Vous pouvez afficher la liste de tous les alias existants par la commande <literal>alias</literal> (voir <literal>bash</literal>(1) sous «&nbsp;COMMANDES INTERNES DU SHELL&nbsp;»)."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:4325
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ alias\n"
"...\n"
"alias la='ls -la'"
msgstr ""
"$ alias\n"
"...\n"
"alias la='ls -la'"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:4328
msgid "You can identity exact path or identity of the command by <literal>type</literal> (see <literal>bash</literal>(1) under \"SHELL BUILTIN COMMANDS\")."
msgstr "Vous pouvez identifier le chemin exact ou identifier la commande par <literal>type</literal> (voir <literal>bash</literal>(1) sous «&nbsp;COMMANDES INTERNES DU SHELL &nbsp;»)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:4330
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ type ls\n"
"ls is hashed (/bin/ls)\n"
"$ type la\n"
"la is aliased to ls -la\n"
"$ type echo\n"
"echo is a shell builtin\n"
"$ type file\n"
"file is /usr/bin/file"
msgstr ""
"$ type ls\n"
"ls is hashed (/bin/ls)\n"
"$ type la\n"
"la is aliased to ls -la\n"
"$ type echo\n"
"echo is a shell builtin\n"
"$ type file\n"
"file is /usr/bin/file"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:4338
msgid "Here <literal>ls</literal> was recently searched while \"<literal>file</literal>\" was not, thus \"<literal>ls</literal>\" is \"hashed\", i.e., the shell has an internal record for the quick access to the location of the \"<literal>ls</literal>\" command."
msgstr "Ici, <literal>ls</literal> a été récemment recherché alors que «&nbsp;<literal>file</literal>&nbsp;» ne l'a pas été, donc «&nbsp;<literal>ls</literal>&nbsp;» est «&nbsp;hachée&nbsp;», c'est-à-dire que l'interpréteur de commandes possède un enregistrement interne permettant un accès rapide à l'emplacement de la commande «&nbsp;<literal>ls</literal>&nbsp;»."

