msgid "ignore as comments (end-of-line comments are <emphasis role=\"strong\">not</emphasis> supported)"
msgstr "est traitée comme commentaire et ignorée (les commentaire de fin de ligne ne sont <emphasis role=\"strong\">pas</emphasis> pris en charge)"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12220
msgid "A line ending with a backslash \"<literal>\\</literal>\""
msgstr "Une ligne se terminant par un anti-slash «&nbsp;<literal>\\</literal>&nbsp;»"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12223
msgid "extend the configuration to the next line"
msgstr "étend la configuration à la ligne suivante"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12229
msgid "Lines started with <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis> stanza has the following syntax."
msgstr "Les lignes commençant par l'entrée <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis> ont la syntaxe suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12230
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"iface &lt;config_name&gt; &lt;address_family&gt; &lt;method_name&gt;\n"
" &lt;option1&gt; &lt;value1&gt;\n"
" &lt;option2&gt; &lt;value2&gt;\n"
" ..."
msgstr ""
"iface &lt;nom_config&gt; &lt;famille_adresse&gt; &lt;nom_méthode&gt;\n"
" &lt;option1&gt; &lt;valeur1&gt;\n"
" &lt;option2&gt; &lt;valeur2&gt;\n"
" ..."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12234
msgid "For the basic configuration, the <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>mapping</literal></emphasis> stanza is not used and you use the network interface name as the network configuration name (See <xref linkend=\"_the_mapping_stanza\"/>)."
msgstr "Pour la configuration de base, l'entrée de <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>mapping</literal></emphasis> n'est pas utilisée si vous utilisez le nom de l'interface réseau comme nom de configuration du réseau (voir <xref linkend=\"_the_mapping_stanza\"/>)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12236
msgid "Do not define duplicates of the \"<literal>iface</literal>\" stanza for a network interface in \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\"."
msgstr "Ne pas définir dans «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp;» d'entrée «&nbsp;<literal>iface</literal>&nbsp;» en double pour une interface réseau"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12240
msgid "The loopback network interface"
msgstr "L'interface réseau de rebouclage («&nbsp;loopback&nbsp;»)"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12241
msgid "The following configuration entry in the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file brings up the loopback network interface <literal>lo</literal> upon booting the system (via <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>auto</literal></emphasis> stanza)."
msgstr "L'entrée de configuration suivante du fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp;» active l'interface réseau «&nbsp;loopback&nbsp;» <literal>lo</literal> lors du démarrage du système (grâce à l'entrée <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>auto</literal></emphasis>)&nbsp;:"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12242 debian-reference.en.xmlt:13027
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"auto lo\n"
"iface lo inet loopback"
msgstr ""
"auto lo\n"
"iface lo inet loopback"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12244
msgid "This one always exists in the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file."
msgstr "Elle existe toujours dans le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp;»."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12247
msgid "The network interface served by the DHCP"
msgstr "Interfaces réseau gérées par DHCP"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12248
msgid "After prepairing the system by <xref linkend=\"_the_dhcp_connection_with_the_ethernet\"/>, the network interface served by the DHCP is configured by creating the configuration entry in the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file as the following."
msgstr "Après avoir préparé le système selon <xref linkend=\"_the_dhcp_connection_with_the_ethernet\"/>, l'interface réseau gérée par le DHCP est configurée en créant l'entrée de configuration suivante dans le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp;»&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12249
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"allow-hotplug eth0\n"
"iface eth0 inet dhcp\n"
" hostname \"mymachine\""
msgstr ""
"allow-hotplug eth0\n"
"iface eth0 inet dhcp\n"
" hostname \"ma_machine\""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12252
msgid "When the Linux kernel detects the physical interface <literal>eth0</literal>, the <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>allow-hotplug</literal></emphasis> stanza causes <literal>ifup</literal> to bring up the interface and the <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis> stanza causes <literal>ifup</literal> to use DHCP to configure the interface."
msgstr "Lorsque le noyau de Linux détecte l'interface physique <literal>eth0</literal>, l'entrée <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>allow-hotplug</literal></emphasis> permet à <literal>ifup</literal> d'activer l'interface et l'entrée <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis> demande à <literal>ifup</literal> d'utiliser DHCP pour configurer l'interface."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12255
msgid "The network interface with the static IP"
msgstr "Interface réseau avec une adresse IP fixe"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12256
msgid "The network interface served by the static IP is configured by creating the configuration entry in the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file as the following."
msgstr "Une interface réseau avec une adresse IP fixe est configurée en créant de la manière suivante une entrée de configuration du fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp;»&nbsp;:"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12257
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"allow-hotplug eth0\n"
"iface eth0 inet static\n"
" address 192.168.11.100\n"
" netmask 255.255.255.0\n"
" broadcast 192.168.11.255\n"
" gateway 192.168.11.1\n"
" dns-domain lan\n"
" dns-nameservers 192.168.11.1"
msgstr ""
"allow-hotplug eth0\n"
"iface eth0 inet static\n"
" address 192.168.11.100\n"
" netmask 255.255.255.0\n"
" broadcast 192.168.11.255\n"
" gateway 192.168.11.1\n"
" dns-domain lan\n"
" dns-nameservers 192.168.11.1"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12265
msgid "When the Linux kernel detects the physical interface <literal>eth0</literal>, the <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>allow-hotplug</literal></emphasis> stanza causes <literal>ifup</literal> to bring up the interface and the <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis> stanza causes <literal>ifup</literal> to use the static IP to configure the interface."
msgstr "Lorsque le noyau de Linux détecte l'interface physique <literal>eth0</literal>, l'entrée <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>allow-hotplug</literal></emphasis> permet à <literal>ifup</literal> d'activer l'interface utiliser l'IP statique pour la configurer."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12266
msgid "Here, I assumed the following."
msgstr "Ici, je suppose ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12270
msgid "IP address range of the LAN network: <literal>192.168.11.0</literal> - <literal>192.168.11.255</literal>"
msgstr "plage d'adresses IP du réseau local&nbsp;: <literal>192.168.11.0</literal> - <literal>192.168.11.255</literal>"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12275
msgid "IP address of the gateway: <literal>192.168.11.1</literal>"
msgstr "adresse IP de la passerelle&nbsp;: <literal>192.168.11.1</literal>"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12280
msgid "IP address of the PC: <literal>192.168.11.100</literal>"
msgstr "adresse IP du PC&nbsp;: <literal>192.168.11.100</literal>"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12285
msgid "The <literal>resolvconf</literal> package: installed"
msgstr "paquet <literal>resolvconf</literal>&nbsp;: installé"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12290
msgid "The domain name: \"<literal>lan</literal>\""
msgstr "nom de domaine&nbsp;: «&nbsp;<literal>lan</literal>&nbsp;»"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12295
msgid "IP address of the DNS server: <literal>192.168.11.1</literal>"
msgstr "adresse IP address du serveur DNS&nbsp;: <literal>192.168.11.1</literal>"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12299
msgid "When the <literal>resolvconf</literal> package is not installed, DNS related configuration needs to be done manually by editing the \"<literal>/etc/resolv.conf</literal>\" as the following."
msgstr "Si le paquet <literal>resolvconf</literal> n'est pas installé, vous devrez faire vous-même la configuration associée au DNS en éditant le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/resolv.conf</literal>&nbsp;» comme suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12300
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"nameserver 192.168.11.1\n"
"domain lan"
msgstr ""
"nameserver 192.168.11.1\n"
"domain lan"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12303
msgid "The IP addresses used in the above example are not meant to be copied literally.  You have to adjust IP numbers to your actual network configuration."
msgstr "Les adresses IP utilisées dans l'exemple ci-dessus ne sont pas destinées à être recopiées littéralement. Vous devrez adapter les adresses IP à la configuration réelle de votre réseau."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12307
msgid "The basics of wireless LAN interface"
msgstr "Les bases de l'interface réseau sans fil"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12308
msgid "The <ulink url=\"&wirelesslanwlanforshort;\">wireless LAN (WLAN for short)</ulink> provides the fast wireless connectivity through the spread-spectrum communication of unlicensed radio bands based on the set of standards called <ulink url=\"&ieeeiacbb;\">IEEE 802.11</ulink>."
msgstr "Le <ulink url=\"&wirelesslanwlanforshort;\">réseau local sans fil</ulink> («&nbsp;wireless LAN ou WLAN&nbsp;») permet une connexion sans fil à haute vitesse par une communication en spectre étalé «&nbsp;spread-spectrum&nbsp;» sur des bandes radio ne nécessitant pas de licence en utilisant un ensemble de normes appelées <ulink url=\"&ieeeiacbb;\">IEEE 802.11</ulink>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12309
msgid "The WLAN interfaces are almost like normal Ethernet interfaces but require some network ID and encryption key data to be provided when they are initialized.  Their high level network tools are exactly the same as that of Ethernet interfaces except interface names are a bit different like <literal>eth1</literal>, <literal>wlan0</literal>, <literal>ath0</literal>, <literal>wifi0</literal>, … depending on the kernel drivers used."
msgstr "Les interfaces WLAN se comportent sensiblement de la même manière que les interfaces ethernet normales mais elles demandent un identifiant de réseau l'on doit fournir des données de clé de chiffrement lors de leur initialisation. Leurs outils réseau de haut niveau sont exactement les mêmes que pour les interfaces ethernet mais les noms des interfaces sont un peu différents, comme <literal>eth1</literal>, <literal>wlan0</literal>, <literal>ath0</literal>, <literal>wifi0</literal>, … selon les pilotes du noyau utilisés."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12311
msgid "The <literal>wmaster0</literal> device is the master device which is an internal device used only by <ulink url=\"&softmac;\">SoftMAC</ulink> with new <ulink url=\"&maciacbbapioflinux;\">mac80211 API of Linux</ulink>."
msgstr "Le périphérique <literal>wmaster0</literal> est le périphérique-maître qui est un périphérique interne utilisé uniquement par <ulink url=\"&softmac;\">SoftMAC</ulink> avec la nouvelle <ulink url=\"&maciacbbapioflinux;\">API mac80211 de Linux</ulink>."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12313
msgid "Here are some keywords to remember for the WLAN."
msgstr "Voici quelques mot-clés à se souvenir pour le WLAN&nbsp;:"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12315
msgid "List of acronyms for WLAN"
msgstr "Liste d'acronymes pour le WLAN"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12326
msgid "full word"
msgstr "en entier"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12336
msgid "NWID"
msgstr "NWID"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12339
msgid "Network ID"
msgstr "ID du réseau"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12342
msgid "16 bit network ID used by pre-802.11 <ulink url=\"&wavelan;\">WaveLAN</ulink> network (very deprecated)"
msgstr "ID du réseau sur 16 bits utilisées par les réseaux <ulink url=\"&wavelan;\">WaveLAN</ulink> pre-802.11 (complètement dépassé)"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12347
