#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20005
msgid "Listing files opened by a process"
msgstr "Afficher les fichier ouverts par un processus"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20006
msgid "You can list all files opened by a process with a process ID (PID), e.g. 1, by the following."
msgstr "Vous pouvez afficher la liste des fichiers ouverts par un processus avec un identifiant de processus (PID), par exemple de 1 en faisant ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20007
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ sudo lsof -p 1"
msgstr "$ sudo lsof -p 1"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20008
msgid "PID=1 is usually <literal>init</literal> program."
msgstr "PID=1 est habituellement le programme <literal>init</literal>."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20011
msgid "Tracing program activities"
msgstr "Tracer l'activité d'un programme"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20012
msgid "You can trace program activity with <literal>strace</literal>(1), <literal>ltrace</literal>(1), or <literal>xtrace</literal>(1) for system calls and signals, library calls, or communication between X11 client and server."
msgstr "Vous pouvez tracer l'activité d'un programme avec <literal>strace</literal>(1), <literal>ltrace</literal>(1) ou <literal>xtrace</literal>(1) pour les appels système, les appels bibliothèque ou la communication entre le serveur et le client X11."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20013
msgid "You can trace system calls of the <literal>ls</literal> command as the following."
msgstr "Vous pouvez tracer les appels système  de la commande <literal>ls</literal> de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20014
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ sudo strace ls"
msgstr "$ sudo strace ls"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20017
msgid "Identification of processes using files or sockets"
msgstr "Identification des processus qui utilisent des fichiers ou des sockets"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20018
msgid "You can also identify processes using files by <literal>fuser</literal>(1), e.g. for \"<literal>/var/log/mail.log</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr "Vous pouvez aussi identifier les processus qui utilisent des fichiers par <literal>fuser</literal>(1), par exemple pour «&nbsp;<literal>/var/log/mail.log</literal>&nbsp;» en faisant ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20019
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo fuser -v /var/log/mail.log\n"
"                     USER        PID ACCESS COMMAND\n"
"/var/log/mail.log:   root       2946 F.... syslogd"
msgstr ""
"$ sudo fuser -v /var/log/mail.log\n"
"                     USER        PID ACCESS COMMAND\n"
"/var/log/mail.log:   root       2946 F.... syslogd"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20022
msgid "You see that file \"<literal>/var/log/mail.log</literal>\" is open for writing by the <literal>syslogd</literal>(8) command."
msgstr "Vous voyez que le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/var/log/mail.log</literal>&nbsp;» est ouvert en écriture par la commande <literal>syslogd</literal>(8)."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20023
msgid "You can also identify processes using sockets by <literal>fuser</literal>(1), e.g. for \"<literal>smtp/tcp</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr "Vous pouvez aussi identifier le processus qui utilisent des sockets par <literal>fuser</literal>(1), par exemple, pour «&nbsp;<literal>smtp/tcp</literal>&nbsp;» par ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20024
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo fuser -v smtp/tcp\n"
"                     USER        PID ACCESS COMMAND\n"
"smtp/tcp:            Debian-exim   3379 F.... exim4"
msgstr ""
"$ sudo fuser -v smtp/tcp\n"
"                     USER        PID ACCESS COMMAND\n"
"smtp/tcp:            Debian-exim   3379 F.... exim4"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20027
msgid "Now you know your system runs <literal>exim4</literal>(8) to handle <ulink url=\"&tcp;\">TCP</ulink> connections to <ulink url=\"&smtp;\">SMTP</ulink> port (25)."
msgstr "Vous savez maintenant que <literal>exim4</literal>(8) tourne sur votre système pour gérer les connexions <ulink url=\"&tcp;\">TCP</ulink> du port <ulink url=\"&smtp;\">SMTP</ulink> (25)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20030
msgid "Repeating a command with a constant interval"
msgstr "Répéter une commande avec un intervalle constant"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20031
msgid "<literal>watch</literal>(1) executes a program repeatedly with a constant interval while showing its output in fullscreen."
msgstr "<literal>watch</literal>(1) execute un programme de manière répétitive avec un intervalle constant tout en affichant sa sortie en plein écran."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20032
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ watch w"
msgstr "$ watch w"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20033
msgid "This displays who is logged on to the system updated every 2 seconds."
msgstr "Ceci permet d'afficher, mis à jour toutes les deux secondes, qui est connecté au système."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20036
msgid "Repeating a command looping over files"
msgstr "Répéter une commande en bouclant entre des fichiers"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20037
msgid "There are several ways to repeat a command looping over files matching some condition, e.g. matching glob pattern \"<literal>*.ext</literal>\"."
msgstr "Il existe plusieurs manières de répéter une boucle de commande entre des fichiers correspondant à une condition, par exemple, correspondant au motif «&nbsp;glob&nbsp;» «&nbsp;<literal>*.ext</literal>&nbsp;»."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20041
msgid "Shell for-loop method (see <xref linkend=\"_shell_loops\"/>):"
msgstr "Méthode de la boucle «&nbsp;for»&nbsp;» de l'interpréteur de commandes (voir <xref linkend=\"_shell_loops\"/>)&nbsp;:"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20045
#, no-wrap
msgid "for x in *.ext; do if [ -f \"$x\"]; then command \"$x\" ; fi; done"
msgstr "for x in *.ext; do if [ -f \"$x\"]; then commande \"$x\" ; fi; done"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20048
msgid "<literal>find</literal>(1) and <literal>xargs</literal>(1) combination:"
msgstr "combinaison de <literal>find</literal>(1) et de <literal>xargs</literal>(1)&nbsp;:"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20052
#, no-wrap
msgid "find . -type f -maxdepth 1 -name '*.ext' -print0 | xargs -0 -n 1 command"
msgstr "find . -type f -maxdepth 1 -name '*.ext' -print0 | xargs -0 -n 1 commande"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20055
msgid "<literal>find</literal>(1) with \"<literal>-exec</literal>\" option with a command:"
msgstr "<literal>find</literal>(1) avec l'option «&nbsp;<literal>-exec</literal>&nbsp;» avec une commande&nbsp;:"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20059
#, no-wrap
msgid "find . -type f -maxdepth 1 -name '*.ext' -exec command '{}' \\;"
msgstr "find . -type f -maxdepth 1 -name '*.ext' -exec commande '{}' \\;"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20062
msgid "<literal>find</literal>(1) with \"<literal>-exec</literal>\" option with a short shell script:"
msgstr "<literal>find</literal>(1) avec l'option «&nbsp;<literal>-exec</literal>&nbsp;» avec un court script de l'interpréteur&nbsp;:"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20066
#, no-wrap
msgid "find . -type f -maxdepth 1 -name '*.ext' -exec sh -c \"command '{}' &amp;&amp; echo 'successful'\" \\;"
msgstr "find . -type f -maxdepth 1 -name '*.ext' -exec sh -c \"commande '{}' &amp;&amp; echo 'succès'\" \\;"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20067
msgid "The above examples are written to ensure proper handling of funny file names such as ones containing spaces.  See <xref linkend=\"_idioms_for_the_selection_of_files\"/> for more advance uses of <literal>find</literal>(1)."
msgstr "Les exemple ci-dessus ont été écrits afin d'assurer une prise en compte correcte de noms de fichiers étranges tels que ceux qui comportent des espaces. Voir <xref linkend=\"_idioms_for_the_selection_of_files\"/> pour une utilisation avancée de <literal>find</literal>(1)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20070
msgid "Starting a program from GUI"
msgstr "Lancer un programme depuis l'interface graphique"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20071
msgid "You can set up to start a process from <ulink url=\"&graphicaluserinterfacegui;\">graphical user interface (GUI)</ulink>."
msgstr "Vous pouvez définir le lancement d'un processus depuis l'<ulink url=\"&graphicaluserinterfacegui;\">interface utilisateur graphique (GUI)</ulink>."

